## Full Worked Example: 1 Day with Remap at 14:00

**Setup:**
- Campaign A: mapped to `binance.com/?ref=ducba` → Project Binance
- Campaign B: mapped to `kling.ai/?ref=toan` → Project Kling
- At **14:00**, user remaps Campaign A → `kling.ai/?ref=ducba` → Project Kling

**Transactions created by hourly sync:**

| TX ID | Time | Campaign | Ref Link | Project | Cost | Clicks | Type |
|-------|------|----------|----------|---------|------|--------|------|
| 0001 | 00:00 | Camp A | ref=ducba@binance | Binance | $180 | 18 | SYNC |
| 0002 | 00:00 | Camp B | ref=toan@kling | Kling | $36 | 10 | SYNC |
| 0003 | 01:00 | Camp A | ref=ducba@binance | Binance | $195 | 20 | SYNC |
| 0004 | 01:00 | Camp B | ref=toan@kling | Kling | $32 | 8 | SYNC |
| ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| 0025 | 13:00 | Camp A | ref=ducba@binance | Binance | $210 | 22 | SYNC |
| 0026 | 13:00 | Camp B | ref=toan@kling | Kling | $38 | 11 | SYNC |
| | **14:00** | | **USER REMAPS Camp A → Kling** | | | | |
| 0027 | 14:00 | Camp A | **ref=ducba@kling** | **Kling** | $205 | 21 | SYNC |
| 0028 | 14:00 | Camp B | ref=toan@kling | Kling | $35 | 9 | SYNC |
| ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| 0047 | 23:00 | Camp A | ref=ducba@kling | Kling | $190 | 19 | SYNC |
| 0048 | 23:00 | Camp B | ref=toan@kling | Kling | $34 | 10 | SYNC |

**End-of-day aggregation:**

| Project | Camp | Hours attributed | Total Cost | Total Clicks |
|---------|------|:---:|-----------|-------------|
| Binance | Camp A | 00:00–13:00 (14h) | **$2,730** | 280 |
| Kling | Camp A | 14:00–23:00 (10h) | **$1,975** | 200 |
| Kling | Camp B | 00:00–23:00 (24h) | **$840** | 234 |

> **No splitting math.** The hourly sync naturally captures the exact remap moment. 
> Binance gets Camp A's spend up to 13:00. Kling gets Camp A's spend from 14:00.
> Total Camp A for the day = $2,730 + $1,975 = $4,705 → **nothing lost, nothing duplicated.**

