## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q8: Snapshot vs reference for campaign/project names?**  
> The schema stores `campaignName` and `projectName` as snapshots. If user renames the project later, old transactions still show the old name. Is this correct behavior (audit accuracy) or should transactions always show current name (display convenience)?

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **Q9: Backfill depth limit?**  
> When user maps a campaign for the first time, how far back should we backfill? Options:
> - (a) All available Google Ads history (~2 years)
> - (b) Max 90 days  
> - (c) Configurable per user/project
> - (d) Since project creation date (most logical?)
